job.plaincontent:
Become a part of Bär & Karrer as a 

Trainee in Zurich, Zug, Lugano and Geneva
"That "we're all in the same boat" feeling in our internship community is just really strong," said a recent aspiring 
lawyer. Indeed, the cohesion between our interns is almost legendary. This certainly has something to do with the 
events, the daily exchange and the many leisure activities. Or with the commitment of our lawyers in the weekly 
trainings for the bar exam. And it is probably also quite simply a reflection of our working atmosphere, which for some 
is surprisingly uncomplicated.
Interesting tasks: 

- Supporting a partner and the associated team of lawyers in really exciting mandates;
- Working on interesting, sometimes large mandates that attract attention beyond the professional world;
- Take on responsibility quickly and work independently but well looked after.

Your profile: 

- Completed law master's degree;
- Fluency in German and English;
- Curiosity to learn a lot in a short time;
- Ambition to make an important contribution to the successful completion of mandates;
- Collegiality and the desire to support other teams in an uncomplicated way if necessary.

An interesting package of advantages for you: 

- One of the most prestigious law firms in Switzerland with an international reputation: with 150 employees well 
positioned for large mandates that cause a sensation, and with our partnership fast and decisive at the same time;
- Teamwork in large mandates with sometimes several teams involved;
- Permanent knowledge updates with one-day seminars or short on-the-job trainings;
- A great deal of freedom in the organisation of working hours and state-of-the-art IT and communication tools;
- Excellent support on the way to being admitted to the bar with many on-the-job learnings and weekly training lunches;
- Beneficial (and perhaps even surprising), uncomplicated interaction with each other and probably the best team 
spirit in the industry;
- You can find many more advantages of a commitment with Bär & Karrer here.



My name is Muriel Riedo, Head HR, and I am happy to serve you. Just give me a call if you have any questions: +41 58 
261 54 72. I look forward to studying your application. Your documents will reach me quickly and securely via our 
online tool.
